manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: ​Ten Pack of Fan Favorite Cars! ​Kids who love Disney and Pixar Cars will have a blast with this 10-pack of beloved character vehicles for storytelling and racing fun! ​Ten Fan Favorites! ​This 10-Pack of movie favorites includes Lightning McQueen, Luigi, Mater, Sally, Bruce Miller RPM #64, Cal Weathers #42, Rusty, Dusty, Brick Yardley #24 and Jackson Storm. Imaginations will race with these delightful characters to help create stories and stage thrilling speed competitions. Die-cast with Authentic Details! 1:55 scale vehicles are the perfect size to take along for on-the-go playtime. Kids 3 years old and up will have a blast recreating their favorite scenes from all the Cars movies.

​A Great Gift for Kids Who Love Cars! ​​Girls and boys who love the Cars movies will have hours of fun racing their new cars around Radiator Springs, the Los Angeles International Speedway, Ornament Valley and any setting they can imagine!​

reviews.reviewText: Overall Rating: ★★★★★ (5 out of 5 stars)Endless Entertainment: The Mattel Disney Pixar Cars Die-Cast Mini Racers 10-Pack has been a huge hit in our household. These miniature racecar toys, based on the beloved Cars movies, have not only provided endless hours of fun for my child but have also sparked an adorable learning journey. My kid now knows all the names of the cars, and, to my own surprise, so do I!Perfectly Sized for Little Hands: The size of these mini racers is just right for small hands. They're easy to play with, carry around, and store, making them perfect for kids age 3 and up. Their portability also means they are great companions for trips and outings.Exceptional Detail and Quality: Each car in the 10-pack is beautifully crafted with attention to detail, closely resembling their movie counterparts. The quality of Mattel's die-cast design is evident, as these toys have withstood the regular play of an enthusiastic toddler without any signs of wear and tear.Collectible and Educational: Beyond being just toys, these mini racers serve as wonderful collectibles for little fans of the Cars franchise. They're also educational, helping my child develop fine motor skills and fueling imaginative play, as each car has its unique personality and story.Ideal Gift for Cars Enthusiasts: For any kid (or parent) who's a fan of the Disney Pixar Cars movies, this set is a dream come true. It's a fantastic gift that combines fun, learning, and a love for these iconic characters.Conclusion: The Mattel Disney Pixar Cars Die-Cast Mini Racers 10-Pack is an outstanding set that delivers in terms of quality, play value, and educational content. It's a delightful way for kids to interact with their favorite characters and for parents to bond with their children over a shared love of these charming racecars.

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars These are High Quality Painted Metal Cars
reviews.reviewText: They come in a box that says they are officially affiliated with the Disney Pixar movie "Cars". It was easy to open the box and slide the plastic holder out, revealing all of the cars. The cars popped out of the plastic holder, and would pop back in to place if you wanted to store them in the box. Once the cars are all out of the container, it is very difficult to know which way is up and which cars go where, so here is a pointer. Tow-Mater is larger, so look for the largest opening and press Tow Mater into that spot with the hood of his truck toward your right hand. Look at the colorful box insert to show which cars to press into their spots around Tow Mater and work your way out with all car hoods pointing to the right. Our problem wasn't getting the cars to fit back in the plastic holder, it was my grandson, who didn't want us to put his cars back so they could go home. We had to agree to let him hold Tow Mater and Lightening McQueen in the car. These roll well, do not make noise when played with, look like they are a little too big to fit on a Hot Wheels track. My 3 year old grandson loved them.

This Disney Cars set was perfect for my 4yr old son. He's obsessed with Lightening McQueen and has watched the movie on repeat for the last 5 months, so this toy car set was a perfect addition to his addiction. The cars are metal and very sturdy. Very impressed with he quality. They are similar in size to Hot Wheels cars, but heavier and slightly wider. Packaging was also fantastic, comes in a movie memorabilia-style box, with a spot for each car. We've saved the box since it's quite nice for storing the cars afterwards.We also purchased the Mack truck hauler separately, so my son loves loading the truck with all the cars and driving them around. Would highly recommend this 10 car set!
